social_posts.post_text: I've shoveled my driveway about half a dozen times this year already, so that means plenty of this is in our future. #powdertothepeople
It's been easy to look back and be thankful for all that 2022 brought me. At the top of the list is following these 4 into the wild blue yonder. #hikingfam

If there's anyone who deserves to be on the nice list, it's Josey. This pup has been a good girl all year and deserves nothing but the best for putting up with all my shenanigans. With the holidays around the corner there's no doubt the gift at the top of her list is a bag of @zukespets Mini Naturals. They are her favorite treat and make hiking off leash a breeze. Happy holidays y'all! #zukespack #livelifeoffleash #ad
A place where even the dead have some killer views.... #bigskycountry
Winter hiking with the lil dudettes isn't always easy, but convincing them we were hiking to the ice castle from Frozen helped, momentarily. #bigskycountry
Looking forward to getting up close and personal with some pow this weekend. Winter is back. #weekendwarrior
This is a friendly reminder that even though it's freezing cold out, you should still go outside after work. #frozennostrils
The weekend is here. Time to head for them hills! #powdertothepeople

Had a blast a few weekends ago racing in my first banked slalom. The vibes and snowstorm conditions made for an all time good day. Absolutely looking forward to doing it again next year and working on my speed game. #fastislooselooseisfast
The colors experienced during a winter sunset change so dramatically and quickly that just a few snaps later the whole scene changes. This is why winter sunsets beat summer sunsets. #goforahike
Go splitboarding with your friends. Bozeman splitfest is this weekend. There's been a steady stream of snow this week. Play it safe and see you on the skin track my friends. #splitboardingistheanswer

Our favorite powderhound turned 7 today. Life has brought a ton of changes in the last seven years, but through all of it she has been our ride or die furball. We are looking forward to many summer hikes this year! #joseytails

Crazy to see so many resorts breaking their all time snowfall records this year. I don't think we'll be putting the garden in anytime soon here in Montana and it hasn't even been a record year for us. #powdertothepeople
Snowboarding is fun, photography is fun. Winter is too long in Montana to not make it fun. #powdertothepeople
Some of us wander elsewhere for a while, but we almost always come back home. Happy 4-06 day Montana, I'll never leave again. #bigskycountry

It was one helluva season and I'm all smiles for the way it ended. We had plenty of powder days, and plenty of days watching these girls progress on snow. It's been a highlight of parenting watching them embrace the challenge and actually ask me to go skiing. We are already looking forward to next year and continuing to grow! #bbowlslidin @bridgerbowl
Roads? Where we're going we don't need roads. #splitboardingistheanswer
Good thing she loves winter, because she's certainly got her fill of it this year. #joseytails

After a solid winter the spring melt will hopefully begin soon. This means plenty of evenings down at the river and Josey is stoked. Proper footwear will make these muddy evenings much more tolerable and our friends @sperry have made some great wet weather boots. The Sperry Sport line allows you to throw sticks, chase the dog, and rock hop all evening without getting wet. Bring on the sun! #sperrysport #ad

Happy mother's day to all you moms out there. You da real MVPs. Melly does a ton for our family and we truly couldn't live this lucky life of ours without her hardwork and dedication. Enjoy the day you fellow moms. #montanamom
I've watched way too many games during the NBA playoffs, Josey says it's time to get off the couch and go for a hike!  #hikingwithdogs

A month or more has passed, but finally editing these photos brought back a flood of memories and almost made me miss winter. The Beehive Banked Slalom was the raddest gathering of people I've experienced in a long time. @kirbygrubaugh and his crew worked their butts off to provide one helluva fun event. The snowboard community stays winning when events like this bring us together. #powdertothepeople
Welcome back summer, we've missed you. #itsstillrainingtho

We went for the mountain biking, but I'll be damned if the views didn't try to steal the show... At least a little bit. My first trip to southern Utah was all it's cracked up to be. It's good to know I can still survive a long weekend on beef jerky, energy goo, and PBR. #bananabreath
Some of the worst mountain bike conditions led to some amazingly beautiful views. Glad I lugged my camera up to snap a few post storm views. #cloudporn
One classic Montana view, three different lenses. #bigskycountry
Go moderately fast, and take conservative chances. #dadbikes

We drove 8 hours and we were still in Montana. That's one big ol' state. The landscapes of the eastern half are much different than the west. I honestly felt like I was on a different planet let alone a different state. #familyroadtrips
When you're doing an early morning road trip and the light hits just right, always pull over. #bigskycountry

Warning: sappy appreciation post incoming. Today marks the last day of stay-at-home-mom life for my incredible wife, Melly. Tomorrow she embarks on her first day of her new job. She has carried our family over the past ~6 years and I couldn't be more grateful for her dedication to every small detail that makes our lives better.

I would given up after 3 days of stay at home parenting. She excelled at it and taught me 1000 things in the process. She now accepted a job that is outside her comfort zone just to help further our families success. I don't mean to brag, but damn, I got me a good one. Having kids isn't easy, but having partners who are unselfish and always looking out for others is one way to make it a helluva lot easier. Cheers to all you hardworking parents out there (and hardworking non parents). Keep grinding and enjoying every moment of success you achieve. #mvpmoms
I'm not sure I'm really ready for it, but man, today sure does feel like fall. Prettiest szn of them all. #braceyourself

I don't really have a fear of heights, I actually quite enjoy being able look over the edge and scare myself. But, there was something about being on a bike after 18 miles on the edge of a 1500ft fall that made my knees weak and my stomach not so stoked. I decided to walk this section and let my ego take back seat. #dontlookdown

Sleeping in a tent you carried into the woods is called backpacking, neat huh? It's fun. But the real question is, when you pack up your tent do you vigorously stuff it back into the sack, or do you neatly fold it and roll it up to place it into the sack? Cuz there's only one correct answer..... #stuffersunite

"If you don't do it this year, you'll be another year older when you do". One of my favorite quotes to celebrate another successful trip around the sun. Lots to be thankful for, lots of adventures still to be had with this crew.

The second best feeling after pulling snowboard and ski boots off? Pulling soggy wading boots off and slipping into some slides. Apres fishing just got a lot more comfy from @xtratuf. #apresfish #sponsored

Certainly was a green-filled riding season. Minimal smokey days meant we had to deal with a few surprise rain storms and some mud. But that's okay, I'll wash my bike daily if it means no fire season. #mtbphotography
Just because the sun has gone to bed doesn't mean the fish have. #nightmoves
Didja hear? It snowed today. A lot. #powdertothepeople
Fertile fall foliage in the foreground from a few fun rides. #mtblove
First light and first snow make for one helluva combo.... If I do say so myself. #paradise
